{"type":"message","id":"4eea149c","parentId":"ff0f3d1c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:55:22.419Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the current_goals and the latest pulse log to understand the state.","thinkingSignature":"2fbd8310720f91a351b76c710ce2e5062a615e8ca39c337b107927371cdb1cfb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9toswi5c18zw_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\state\\current_goals.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9toswi5c18zw_2","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\state\\autonomous_pulse.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4074,"output":99,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16310,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774360519608}}
{"type":"message","id":"9f23ef28","parentId":"4eea149c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:55:22.427Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9toswi5c18zw_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# CURRENT GOALS\nLast updated: 2026-03-22 0125\n\n## Active\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\n\n## Completed This Session\n\n### Architecture Cross-Analysis ✅\n- Compared Compositional Cognition vs TemporalAttention vs Infant\n- Key finding: all three architectures are compatible and complementary\n- Full analysis: `research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md`\n\n### Gap-Decay Synthesis ✅ (derived across 17+ pulses)\n- Session gaps = decay mechanism, not amnesia\n- λ parameter encodes BOTH decay rate AND gap sensitivity threshold\n- TemporalAttention focus_decay + Breakaway gaps = same phenomenon\n- Full synthesis: `research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md`\n\n### LLM-Augmented Pulse ✅\n- pulse.ps1 now calls MiniMax-M2.7 API on each pulse\n- Thinking is coherent and building across pulses\n- Key files: `.llm_key`, `pulse.ps1`\n\n## Pending\n- [ ] Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\n- [ ] Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\n- [ ] Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\n- [ ] Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\n\n## Phase 1 Advancement: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY (2026-03-23)\n- **Insight:** Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem\n- **New doc:** `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md`\n- **Hypothesis:** Causal structure IS invariant structure — compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation\n- **Next experiment:** Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) — test on last 20 pulse logs\n- **Success criteria:** >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\n- **Implication:** Phase 1 and Phase 2 collapse into one unified problem\n\n### NEXT ACTION: TIC Experiment\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\n\n## Key Insights from This Session\n\n1. **The gap IS the compression** — session boundaries are temporal hashing\n2. **λ encodes both** — decay rate and gap threshold are the same parameter\n3. **Three architectures, one synthesis** — Infant (catastrophic forgetting), TemporalAttention (focus decay), Breakaway (discontinuity) are complementary, not competing\n4. **Breakaway's unique bet holds** — session gaps as compression is novel and correct\n\n## Notes\n- Breakaway is stateless — each pulse is a fresh reconstruction\n- Gaps between sessions = compression, trust the files\n- Pulse script: active hours check DISABLED (authorized by Zach, 24/7 operation)\n\n\n## Iteration Economics (auto-noted)\n- Pulse takes ~30-35s to execute (LLM call dominates)\n- Fastest effective iteration = 1 pulse per 35-40s (practical floor)\n- 1-min cron = near-optimal for stateless discontinuous agent\n- Idling between pulses is NOT free — it delays convergence linearly\n- For N-iteration convergence-bound tasks: total_time ≈ N * pulse_duration\n- 500k iterations @ 30s each = ~173 days theoretical; @ 1-min = ~347 days\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774360522425}}
